everyone always thinks that life for all the other stereotypical groups is so much easier.  what im trying to say is the foyer ratss all think that life is so easy for the jocks and the cheerleaders, while they are thinking that life would be so much easier if they just gave up like the others.  

but what happens if you dont belong to a specific group?  i feel that way alot...
for example i play football, however i am also in all honors classes.  its not like that hasnt been done before, but i dont rilly feel like i belong to the whole jock group at all.  then i do gymnastics so i am in that whole group, while maintaining the whole local scene.  if you know anything about any of these groups than you can begin to see how confusing life can be.  i dont feel like i have one specific area that i can focus on in my life.  it gets way too confusing.  

i rilly begin to hate life sometimes, but there is too much to live for to die; too many parties i havent gone to, too many girls i havent met yet, too many times to goof off in class.
